comments.body:
From my understanding, seems like you are expecting `TriggerAsync()` to work like **fire-and-forget** but the actual implementation does not work that way.

For example,
``` c#
  // line 1
  Trigger(eventSource, eventDate);
  // line 3
```
We are excepting when the execution hit `line 3` all event handlers must have been triggered and completed synchonorously during the `Trigger()` call.

This goes the same for `TriggerAsync()`.
``` c#
  // line 1
  await TriggerAsync(eventSource, eventDate);
  // line 3
```
When the execution hit `line 3` all event handlers must have been triggered and completed asynchronously

