Hi,

Are you also using EF?

If you inject IRepository&lt;YourEntity&gt; ABP can no know which repository is used.

For EF, it gets your DbContext and find all DbSet properties to find related entities. Then for reach entity, it creates a repository. So, if your entity (say, Person) is not in a dbcontext then it can not be injected using IRepository&lt;Person&gt;

If you have a base repository class for redis, you can register IRepository&lt;T&gt; for RedisRepository&lt;T&gt;

