DefaultNameOrConnectionString is the default one. It's suitable if you are using only one DbContext. If you have two dbcontext, create empty contructors for dbcontexes and pass your conn string to base class. Sample:

```
public class SampleApplicationDbContext : AbpDbContext
{
    public virtual IDbSet<Person> People { get; set; }

    public SampleApplicationDbContext()
        : base("MyConnectionStringOne")
    {

    }
}
```

For second dbcontext, pass second conn string.

Hi @bernardo5304 

You can use SignalR with dependency injection. It's not a special thing to ABP. You can find resources on web.

I'm using SignalR with ABP (hosted in Windows Service). This is my Owin startup configuration:

```
internal class Startup
{
    public void Configuration(IAppBuilder app)
    {
        GlobalHost.DependencyResolver = new WindsorDependencyResolver();

        app.UseCors(CorsOptions.AllowAll);
        app.MapSignalR();
    }
}
```

And this is the  WindsorDependencyResolver class:

```
public class WindsorDependencyResolver : DefaultDependencyResolver
{
    public override object GetService(Type serviceType)
    {
        return IocManager.Instance.IocContainer.Kernel.HasComponent(serviceType) ? IocManager.Instance.IocContainer.Resolve(serviceType) : base.GetService(serviceType);
    }

    public override IEnumerable<object> GetServices(Type serviceType)
    {
        return IocManager.Instance.IocContainer.Kernel.HasComponent(serviceType) ? IocManager.Instance.IocContainer.ResolveAll(serviceType).Cast<object>() : base.GetServices(serviceType);
    }
}
```

If you can not do, search using castle windsor with signalr.

